text:
"I still don‚Äôt get it. MAPPA knows how massive and popular Jujutsu Kaisen is‚Äîso why don‚Äôt they boost the animation quality like they did with Chainsaw Man (CSM)? Back during its development, MAPPA opened a new branch focused on CGI to improve their work environment and production flow .

Even the president called CSM their most ambitious project yet . Still, despite having a massive fanbase and being arguably the most popular new sh≈çnen anime, Jujutsu Kaisen Season 3‚Äôs animation feels disappointing compared to what CSM delivered.

I can‚Äôt comprehend what the director‚Äôs aiming for or what his marketing strategy is. If the goal is profit, they should follow Demon Slayer‚Äôs lead with a movie‚Äîlike the Infinity Castle arc. It was a smart move by Ufotable, even though the franchise‚Äôs author didn‚Äôt get major profit‚Äîso most of the money went to the studio . It shows how wise marketing strategy can pay off massively.

I just hope MAPPA gets sharper with marketing and really does their research.

The trailer for Jujutsu Kaisen dropped, and in that very moment the clouds parted, sunlight poured through my window, and the air tasted sweeter than it had in years. My hands stopped trembling, the bottles on the floor vanished as if exorcised, and for the first time since childhood, I smiled. Suddenly the birds outside began singing in harmony, my landlord forgave my rent, and even my reflection in the mirror whispered, ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs going to be okay.‚Äù My life has been reborn.
